  "market_context": "Tesla was in an uptrend with recent strong impulsive moves; the analyst used the 'All Chart Patterns' indicator on the daily chart to automatically detect and analyze multiple patterns including rising wedge, falling wedge, and inverse head-and-shoulders.",
  "key_observation": "The auto chart pattern indicator identified a bearish rising wedge (tightening range with higher highs/lows) that broke downward, and a bullish falling wedge (tightening range with lower highs/lows) that broke upward—both with automatically generated price targets.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst switched to Tesla's daily chart and applied the 'All Chart Patterns' indicator to display all detected patterns and their automatic price targets.",
    "Step 2: The analyst pointed out a rising wedge pattern (green shaded triangle) where price made higher highs and higher lows with narrowing range, identifying it as bearish upon breakdown.",
    "Step 3: The analyst noted the rising wedge breakdown occurred and the indicator generated a target level near 249.22–249.68, which price later reached.",
    "Step 4: The analyst highlighted a falling wedge pattern (red shaded triangle) where price made lower highs and lower lows with tightening range, identifying it as a bullish continuation pattern upon breakout.",
    "Step 5: The analyst emphasized combining these patterns with trend context (buying pullbacks in an uptrend) to increase trade probability, noting falling wedges near support act as additional confirmation."
  ],
  "outcome": "The rising wedge breakdown target (~249.22–249.68) was reached quickly after the breakout; the falling wedge breakout target was also shown but no explicit trade execution or result was stated.",
  "lessons": "Automated chart pattern detection can efficiently identify high-probability setups like rising/falling wedges; however, their reliability improves when combined with trend context and confluence (e.g., support levels, pullbacks).",
